The paper proposes a novel approach for computing Pareto-optimal journeys in a public transit network, which involves modeling trips and transfers between them. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the algorithmic approach, data structures (cs.DS) for the modeling of trips and transfers, machine learning (cs.LG) for the optimization of the Pareto-optimal journeys, social and information networks (cs.SI) for the study of public transit networks, and information theory (cs.IT) for the analysis of the computational complexity of the algorithm.
